column1:
We were on that ship forever... I still feel like
I'm on the waves.

It was quite the rare experience, being
surrounded by the dazzling sea like that.

So this is Kukojima, huh? There are more
people than I expected.

Right? I was picturing something closer to an
untouched island than all this.

This actually was a pretty quiet place until just
a few years ago...

But eventually some folks cooked up a mass
migration plan. They even had a slogan:
"Find your new tropical life."

All of a sudden, a population under 200 people
suddenly explodes to nearly a thousand.

The port area is really quite lively. It has a bit
of a resort feel to it.
Sounds like summer vacation's back on!

C'mon, you know we're not here to screw
around.

First thing we do is head for the research
facility.

He's right, we should start there. I'd like to
get the investigation underway as soon as
possible.
There go the two cops again!
We don't really have a choice.
The case has to come first.
Let's just get it over with.

We can enjoy our free time here once the case
is solved.
Our current objective is the lab Ichinose found.
Okay, let's go! Um... Which way?
Hit us with the deets, Sophia!

I wasn't able to find any information regarding
the facility.

Well, Ichinose did say it wasn't exactly on the
level, right? Maybe we just have to track it down
ourselves.

If that's the case, we should ask around and see
if we can find any locals who know about it.

Who do you think we should ask first? Oh,
maybe the shopkeepers know something?

Ooh, I spy a souvenir shop! I'm gonna buy
somethin' for Sojiro!
Wait, Futaba! I'll join you in the search for native crafts!

It seems we need to ask around
for directions to the lab...
